sec.p:
The final prediction $\hat{y}$ is the average of individual tree outputs:
\begin{equation*}
\hat{y}=\frac{1}{T} \sum_{t=1}^{T} h_{t}(x)
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}

Each tree $h_{t}(x)$ partitions the feature space into disjoint regions $\left\{R_{t, j}\right\}$ and assigns a constant value to each region based on the average of training samples falling in that region:
\begin{equation*}
h_{t}(x)=\sum_{j=1}^{J_{t}} \hat{y}_{t, j} \cdot \nVdash_{\left\{x \in R_{t, j}\right\}}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}
where:

•
$J_{t}$ is the number of leaves in tree $t$,
•
$\hat{y}_{t, j}=\frac{1}{\left\vertR_{t, j}\right\vert} \sum_{x_{i} \in R_{t, j}} y_{i}$ is the mean response in leaf $j$,
•
$\nVdash_{\{\cdot\}}$ is the indicator function.
